<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="285" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d285">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">612.119/2840</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum of a Conversation between the Secretary
                                of State and the Mexican Chargé</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Diego-Fernandez</hi>), <hi rend="italic">April 15, 1920</hi></head>
                        <dateline>
                            <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1920-04-15">April 15, 1920</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p>The Chargé d’Affaires of Mexico again called attention to the shipment of
                            arms across our frontier which might be consigned to or eventually reach
                            the rebellious element in Mexico.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>